<h2>
    Top Salmon Fishing Rivers Near Gresham, Oregon
</h2>
<h3>
    Sandy River
</h3>
<p>
    Just 15 minutes from downtown Gresham, the Sandy River is a salmon magnet. Known for strong spring and fall Chinook runs, it's ideal for both bank and drift boat anglers. Popular access points include Oxbow Regional Park and Dabney State Recreation Area.
</p>
<h3>
    Columbia River (Troutdale Area)
</h3>
<p>
    This mighty river offers boaters and shore anglers a shot at trophy salmon. Focus on areas near the mouth of the Sandy and I-84 boat ramps. Trolling with herring or spinners is highly productive here.
</p>
<h3>
    Clackamas River
</h3>
<p>
    Flowing just south of Gresham, the Clackamas River provides strong fall Coho and Chinook returns. Popular bank access spots include Carver Park and Riverside Park. Drift boaters target deeper runs near Barton and McIver Park.
</p>
